<h1>Problem 936 - 2018 IMOSL, G4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>A point \(T\) is chosen inside a triangle \(ABC\). Let \(A_1\), \(B_1\), and \(C_1\) be the reflections of \(T\) in \(BC\), \(CA\), and \(AB\), respectively. Let \(\Omega\) be the circumcircle of the triangle \(A_1B_1C_1\). The lines \(A_1T\), \(B_1T\), and \(C_1T\) meet \(\Omega\) again at \(A_2\), \(B_2\), and \(C_2\), respectively. Prove that the lines \(AA_2\), \(BB_2\), and \(CC_2\) are concurrent on \(\Omega\).</p>
